Target: An ontology developed for describing reaction experiment.

Comment: A reaction experiment is a concrete realisation of a chemical reaction at a set of reaction conditions.
A reaction variation is defined as the same chemical reaction performed at a different set of reaction conditions compared to its original conditions.
A ChemicalReaction converts some ChemicalSpecies (or MolecularEntities) into some other ChemicalSpecies (or MolecularEntities). [OntoCAPE]
A substance that increases the rate of a reaction without modifying the overall standard Gibbs energy change in the reaction. [doi:10.1351/goldbook.C00876]
A solvent is the substance used to solve the chemical components of the chemical reaction process.
A name-quantity pair that defines the name and corresponding stoichiometric coefficient of a chemical species or molecular entity participating in the reverse reaction. [OntoKin]
The product that is the desired outcome of a reaction experiment.
The product that is not the desired outcome of a reaction experiment.
A quantity that is calculated from the measured analytical data of output chemical of a reaction experiment. It is used as objectives of a reaction optimisation problem.
The environmental factor (E-factor) of a reaction experiment is the ratio of the mass of waste (impurity) to mass of (desired/target) product. [doi:10.1039/B713736M]
Ratio expressing the efficiency of a mass conversion process. [doi:10.1351/goldbook.Y06724]

The conversion indicates, which portion of the originally used starting material has been converted into other chemical substances by a chemical reaction. [UDM https://github.com/PistoiaAlliance/UDM/blob/master/Docs/Glossary.md]
Space-time yield is a measure of reactor productivity calculated from mass of (desired/target) product formed, devided by the the reactor volume, and residence time. [doi:10.1002/cmtd.202000044]
The total cost of input chemical during one reaction experiment.
A quantity that is used to specify the condition at which the reaction is to be conducted. It can be used as the optimisation variable in a reaction development process.

The time required for air or reagent parcel to pass from the entrance to the exit of an instrument. Often this is approximated as the ratio of the interior volume of the device to the flow rate. [doi:10.1351/goldbook.R05309]
The temperature at which a reaction experiment is conducted.
The pressure at which a reaction experiment is conducted.
The ratio between an input chemical and the reference input chemical which is quantified by a reaction scale.
Reaction scale indicates the volume used of the reference input chemical.
An input chemical is a type of OntoCAPE:Material used as the feed to a reaction experiment.
An output chemical is a type of OntoCAPE:Material collected as outcome from a reaction experiment.

A SinglePhase is a finite volume of material within which the physical properties are uniformly constant, i.e., do not experience any abrupt change in passing from one point in the volume to another. [OntoCAPE]
StateOfAggregation describes the physical state of a SinglePhase; solid, liquid, and gaseous are predefined instances of StateOfAggregation. [OntoCAPE]
A PhaseComponent represents the occurrence of a ChemicalComponent in a PhaseSystem. [OntoCAPE]
Composition represents the composition of a SinglePhase by assembling the concentrations of the different PhaseComponents that constitute a single phase. [OntoCAPE]
PhaseComponentConcentration subsumes the different concentration measures for a certain PhaseComponent within a PhaseSystem. [OntoCAPE]
A PhysicalContext of a PhaseSystem is a set of IntensiveThermodynamicStateProperties with known values which are sufficient for determining other Properties of interest of the PhaseSystem. [OntoCAPE]
Volume-BasedConcentration denotes the concentration of a certain PhaseComponent in a PhaseSystem with respect to the colume of PhaseSystem. [OntoCAPE]
The Molarity (aka amount concentration) is the molar amount of a PhaseComponent divided by the volume of the SinglePhase. [OntoCAPE]

A ChemicalSpecies represents pure Substances at the macroscopic scale. It consists of an “ensemble of chemically identical molecular entities […]. The term is applied equally to a set of chemically identical atomic or molecular structural units in a solid array. […] The wording of the definition […] is intended to embrace both cases such as graphite, sodium chloride or a surface oxide, where the basic structural units may not be capable of isolated existence, as well as those cases where they are.” (McNaught & Wilkinson, 1997). [OntoCAPE]
A relation between a reaction experiment and its variation.
A relation links a variation to its parent reaction experiment.
A relation indicates the experiment setup where a reaction experiment happened.
A relation between a reaction experiment and the chemical reaction it represents.
A relation between a chemical reaction and its concrete reaction experiment realisation.
The relation hasCatalyst denotes the catalysts of a ChemicalReaction. A catalyst is a MolecularEntity or a ChemicalSpecies that is used to accelerate a ChemicalReaction.
The relation hasSolvent denotes the solvents of a ChemicalReaction. A solvent is a MolecularEntity or a ChemicalSpecies that is used to host a ChemicalReaction.
A relation between a ChemicalReaction and a named reaction class it belongs to.
A relation between a reaction experiment and the performance indicator calculated from the measured analytical data of its output chemical.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its environmental factor performance indicator.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its yield performance indicator.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its eco score performance indicator.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its conversion performance indicator.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its space time yield performance indicator.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its run material cost performance indicator.
A relation between a reaction experiment and all its reaction conditions.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its residence time condition.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its reaction temperature condition.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its reaction pressure condition.
A relation between a reaction experiment and the stoichiometry ratio it applies to each input chemical.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its reaction scale specified to an input chemical.
A relation indicates the multiplicity of the input chemical participating in a reaction experiment.
A relation indicates the reaction scale in form of usage of an input chemical.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its input chemicals.
A relation between a reaction experiment and its output chemicals.
The relation links a phase system to a material. [OntoCAPE]
The relation designates the aspect system which represents the thermodynamic behavior of some material. [OntoCAPE]
A relation establishes the relationship between a chemical species and the phase component it represents.
The relation hasStateOfAggregation indicates the state of aggregation of a single phase. [OntoCAPE]
The relation isComposedOfSubsystem indicates the non-sharable, direct subsystem of a supersystem. [OntoCAPE]
A relation between a phase system and its composition.
The relation comprisesDirectly indicates the direct members of a property set. [OntoCAPE]
A relation between a phase system and its physical context.
The relation hasProperty indicates the properties of a system. [OntoCAPE]

The relation representsOccurenceOf establishes the relationship between a phase component and the corresponding chemical component, or between a phase reaction and the corresponding chemical reaction. [OntoCAPE]
